reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The Right Part for the Job
reviews.reviewText: This hard drive caddy securely holds a 3.5 inch hard drive, and facilitates installation in a Dell desktop case. That’s precisely my purpose, and it does it really well.The caddy has posts that fit in the drive’s mounting holes - you flex the whole caddy to get the posts to line up with the holes - and it slides into Dell’s proprietary(ish) slide-in mounts, latching securely.It’s a simple device, but it has to fit both the drive and the mounting rails, so it’s sort of important to get the right part. This is it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect fit, flexed to allow pins to enter the mounting holes without incident.
reviews.reviewText: If this is not an OEM part, you would never know it. The one I got still had a good amount of flex to it. I have broken several of these brackets either because they become brittle with age and crack when flexed to insert or remove a drive, or because the pins pop out of the plastic breaking the little retaining tooth. I did not feel like either case was going to be a problem with this caddie. I would (and probably actually will) purchase this again.
